30|$|Product costs {{consist of}} the costs {{involved}} in the purchase or production of goods, including the direct material, <b>direct</b> <b>labor</b> <b>cost</b> and manufacturing overhead. Direct material includes raw materials that can be processed into products. In power plants, direct material cost {{is directly related to}} fuel price. <b>Direct</b> <b>labor</b> <b>cost</b> is the wages paid to workers who produce the products and is directly related to social average wages of the industry. The remaining cost belongs to the manufacturing overhead, which is mainly influenced by the price level.|$|E
40|$|This {{research}} was conducted at the company engaged {{in the business of}} convection, with the title "Analysis of <b>Direct</b> <b>Labor</b> <b>Cost</b> Control in the Production Department PT. Enchantment of Malang Industry Teens. " The {{purpose of this study was}} to determine the <b>direct</b> <b>labor</b> <b>cost</b> control at PT. Enchantment of Malang Industry Teenagers already efficient or not. This type of research is a descriptive case studies with quantitative secondary data sources and analysis used to determine the <b>direct</b> <b>labor</b> <b>cost</b> control is the analysis of variance, the benchmark for determining that control direct labor costs at PT. Enchantment of Malang Industry Teenagers have been effective or not. The results computed by the analysis of this variant was shown that controlling labor costs directly to the PT. Teens Enchantment of Malang Industry has not been effective, so influential at the level of cost efficiency of production. This is evidenced by the deviations of the direct labor costs during 2004, 2005 and 2006. These deviations occur because of several factors including: the determination of the difference is quite high wage rates than the regional minimum wage (UMR), direct labor is not doing the job correctly, the lack of oversight that led to the existence of idle time. Based on the results of this study concluded that for the sake of <b>direct</b> <b>labor</b> <b>cost</b> control company should conduct an analysis of the factors causing the difference is not profitable, so it can take corrective measures that benefit the company. Power technician should check the machine and equipment used in the production process whether it was proper to use or no damage, so that in the production process, capable of generating units in accordance with a production target has been set, and providing training to workers, especially labor technicians. And further enhance the direct monitoring of worker activities (supervision) enforce work discipline and motivation of employees...|$|E
